The party is not always written with red numbers
In Hungary the law precisely defines the days that are written with red numbers on the calendar and has already become a widespread practice that around the holidays - that next year will be less - the working days are reorganized.
Even in the EU or North America, parties are not unitary.
Hungarian laws make a difference between a national holiday, a state holiday and a public holiday.
The festive days are mainly related to religious festivals and historical ephemeris.
Let us also celebrate the New Year: both the last day of the old year and the first day of the new year is festive - the latter especially so that those who spent celebrating the old year can rest.
Throughout the year we have eleven parties written with red numbers on the calendar.
It is a national holiday on March 15 in memory of the 1848 revolution and October 23, commemorative day of the 1956 revolution.
On August 20 we celebrate the foundation of the State, on May 1 the Labor Day, on November 1 and 2, we remember our deceased family and friends.
In addition, in our country there are two-day feasts, Easter of Resurrection, Pentecost and Christmas.
According to the calendar, our state, national or religious holidays rarely coincide with a weekend, so it is often bridged when there is only one working day before or after the holiday.
In exchange for the weekends so extended, during the previous Saturdays you can not be absent from work or school.
It is the minister of labor who regulates in his specific decree when it is necessary to work exactly in exchange for the day directly preceding or after the feast.
This legal standard is mandatory for all employers and their employees, as well as for employees and public officials.
On the other hand, it is not mandatory for companies and service institutions that, due to their function, work uninterruptedly even during holidays.
This year the order of work can be altered only around the holidays of the end of the year: from December 24 practically life in the country is stopped, since according to the experiences, most people "bridge" during the days between Christmas and the end of the year or take their vacation during these days.
Next year several of our holidays will coincide with midday or weekends, so there will be fewer changes in working days than this year.
First, the agenda around the work party will be modified so that then, for four consecutive days, workers can rest.
Saturday, April 26 will be a working day, so that in return on Friday, May 2 will be a festive day.
The other change is related to the party of October 23: on Saturday, October 18, we will have to work instead of Friday, October 24.
On the other hand, next year during the end of the year holiday you can rest, since from December 24th you will not work anywhere, even if the last day of the year is a Wednesday.
Six Little Disturbs to Bite the Lives of Your Colleagues
Emails that we forget to send, sound messages that we never receive, innocent lies that pass us by without realizing it: they are all part of our everyday folklore at work.
You have to decide whether to adapt to the small annoyances or consciously avoid the confusing situations that can annoy others.
Advice.
Sorry, I forgot to tell you that you were picked up by the marketing department," says one of your colleagues.
That's why you didn't go on a date?
At best he feels it and tries to fix the matter, he may call the marketing department to tell them he forgot to deliver the message (this is the less common solution).
Most of the time the issue is resolved by apologizing.
Before proceeding to gloomy explanations, it is worth meditating on the things with which you can embitter the lives of your colleagues and consciously strive to avoid them.
Do you borrow something that is not yours?
There’s nothing more annoying than when you want to grab a document, an office handbook, or your phone and can’t find it.
Remember you put the stapler on the table yesterday, but it's gone by this morning?
Can you find your lost pen on the table of one of your colleagues?
Don’t take anything away from your colleagues without asking them, because they will rightly be angry with you for subtracting their things.
Do not pick up envelopes or post-it from the office because it may be unpleasant when you need them immediately and they are exhausted ahead of time.
Do you gossip about the privacy of your colleagues?
There is no good solution to stop rumors that are already running.
Who, what are you doing and with whom?
Where and why?
Do not pass on to everyone the information (conjectures) you have about the private life of your colleagues!
Don’t abuse your colleague’s trust when they share their most intimate secrets with you!
Bury in yourself what you have heard and do not gossip about your colleague in his absence, although others also know the things about him.
Are you unreasonably on sick leave?
When you call the office and say that you are sick and you have an unbearable headache, you feel bad or well, you feel that on that day you prefer to rest; think about what others should do your work, your impossible tasks, your work by term.
Don't bother your colleague!
If you already know in advance that the next day you will not go to the office or something may happen to you, so you must stay at home, communicate them, so that your colleagues or your boss do not have to face your absence the next day.
Tears, laughter, phone calls
Are you involved in your work, but are you suddenly drawn out of it by the laughter of your colleagues?
Have you involuntarily heard a phone conversation that would have been better not to hear it?
Don’t bother your colleagues with your taunts, chants, loud conversations (unless you do them over your head), pat them, constant blasphemies, expressing your discontent out loud.
All of these can be annoying, even if they are not deepening at this time in a project (writing, planning, organization).
Do you blame others for a mistake?
Don’t blame others if you didn’t finish something on time, forgot to send an important letter or message!
Don’t allude to the eventual chaos in the office, or the noise your colleagues make!
You must recognize if you have made a mistake that harms others and you must repair the fault!
Ask how you can fix your lack!
Do you feel too much at home in the office?
Jogging and shoes: very comfortable habit for the house, but not suitable for the office!
Do not wear a comfortable jogging even if your occupation allows it!
Do not be disorganized, respect your colleagues and yourself by wearing everyday clothes, elegant and beautiful when your occupation so requires!
