Russia has 53 billionaires making a total of $282 billion, according to the Forbes list of the richest people.
In addition, the second-grade rich include 103,000 Russian millionaires whose money reaches $670 billion, according to a study of the evolution of personal wealth in the former Soviet Union, written by economists at the Center for Economic and Financial Research, a local think-thank.
(The World Bank says that in 2005, 15.8% of Russians were below the subsistence level.)
"There are hundreds of millionaires in Moscow - and that's why we're all here," says Nicole Marais, sales and marketing representative for David Morris, the London jeweller.
She attends the fair for the first time with the Russian distributor of the brand, the Soho Jewelry group.
“Women are flawlessly prepared and men are very worthy.”
