United Internet will be the largest shareholder of Versatel.
United Internet secured more than 20 percent of the shares of telecommunications company Versatel.
On Wednesday, the company reported that the average price per share is 14,46 euros.
It has only 20.05 percent of the share capital.
There was much speculation about the company's absorption.
There are also options to further increase the financial share in Versatel.
United Internet reported that with this step it wants to accelerate the consolidation of the German DSL (Digital Subscriber Line) market.
On Wednesday they already made assumptions about entering the business, after Brendenberg bank increased its stake in the Duesseldorf network operator by 5 percent to 15.1 percent.
In the financial market this means that the financial institution holds the equity securities for a third-party partner.
United Internet already on the previous day involved almost 10 percent of the telecommunications company Drillisch.
Drillisch in the capital expansion measure placed 17.4 million of the new shares that have a value of 106.4 million euros.
United Internet has bought 5.15 million shares for 31.4 million euros.
In addition, the companies began negotiations on DSL-product marketing cooperations.
“We are strengthening our collaboration,” a United Internet spokesman said.
The two companies founded an MSP joint venture to acquire competitor Freenet.
On Thursday, United Internet reported that at first, the two companies want to be happy with Freenet’s ten percent stake and do not make use of their right, i.e. they involve 18.49 percent of Freenet.
That meant that both companies retained all options, especially participation in the Freenet anonymous society.
Negotiations between United Internet and Freenet on a strategic partnership ended in mid-November.
This "game" with Freenet that will last for many months and is not very understandable is part of the consolidation of the German Telecom market.
At the end of the third quarter, Freenet had 2.9 million customers with a mobile phone contract and 1.27 million with a DSL contract or full contract.
Until now, the holding company of United Internet and Drillisch had a direct 6.01 percent stake in Freenet.
Then they had agreed that Drillisch was going to get the other four percent.
The right to buy 18.49 percent of the investment company Vatas was already agreed in August.
